An independent investigation panel allegations of human rights violations by the disbanded special anti-robbery squad and other units of the Nigeria police, has ordered National Drug Laws Enforcement Agency (NDLEA), to produce incarcerated police officer, Abba Kyari. This was disclosed by John Martins, representing the chairman of the panel, Justice Suleiman Galadima, stating that a petitioner’s witness had earlier mentioned Kyari in his testimony. “The witness testified that Kyari allegedly promised to reach out to him in respect of the missing persons and till date nothing was heard about them. IGP Reacts To Death Of Egbunike, DIG Investigating Abba Kyari Malami Blocking Abba Kyari’s Extradition – HURIWA “The above orders is made in respect of three persons who were allegedly arrested and detained by the IGP-IRT detention facility. “The whereabouts of Yakubu Danjuma, Ibrahim Daniel and Choji Dung are still unknown,” he said. The panel also ordered that the new commandant of the IGP-IRT, Tunde Disu, must ensure that Kyari is press before the panel on March 22, 2022.